10:10.610 --> 10:11.828
♪♪

10:11.959 --> 10:14.396
[Crowd shouting]

10:14.526 --> 10:15.963
Come on.
Let's go.

10:16.093 --> 10:19.793
♪♪

10:19.923 --> 10:21.621
[Shouting continues]

10:35.330 --> 10:36.810
<i>Madame.</i>

10:47.734 --> 10:56.612
♪♪

10:56.743 --> 11:05.708
♪♪

11:05.839 --> 11:08.624
[Men shouting in French]

11:08.755 --> 11:16.023
♪♪

11:16.153 --> 11:17.372
Nice one, mate.

11:17.502 --> 11:18.460
♪♪

11:18.590 --> 11:20.418
What?

11:20.549 --> 11:22.290
It's just a burn.
It's fine.

11:22.420 --> 11:24.292
It's nothing.
I don't even feel it.

11:24.422 --> 11:25.815
You sure?

11:25.946 --> 11:27.382
Yeah.

11:27.512 --> 11:30.385
Should we stand here
taking the piss or should we go?

11:38.698 --> 11:44.529
[Door opens]

11:44.660 --> 11:46.706
Aah!

11:52.146 --> 11:54.365
[Man grunts]

11:57.412 --> 11:59.501
[Footsteps approaching]

12:22.742 --> 12:25.092
[Down-tempo music plays]

12:25.222 --> 12:27.442
♪♪

12:37.234 --> 12:39.410
[Music continues]

12:50.595 --> 12:53.860
♪♪

12:53.990 --> 12:55.862
[Lock clicking]

12:58.734 --> 13:00.214
Wait. I --
Man, get up!

13:00.344 --> 13:01.476
I just got to rest
for a second.

13:01.606 --> 13:02.869
I told you.
I ain't dying here, man.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.348
Get the fuck up!
You got to die somewhere.

13:04.479 --> 13:06.394
What does it matter
where?

13:06.524 --> 13:08.222
It matters to me.

13:11.529 --> 13:14.402
[Metal clanking]

13:16.839 --> 13:18.623
You know,
I was terrible to her.

13:20.103 --> 13:22.932
Izzy.

13:23.063 --> 13:24.934
I thought I'd get it right
the next time around,

13:25.065 --> 13:27.067
and I made it worse.

13:27.197 --> 13:28.372
Yeah.

13:28.503 --> 13:30.157
Using your own kid
to get her back?

13:30.287 --> 13:33.508
Yeah. Well, I, uh, I didn't
see it like that, did I?

13:39.296 --> 13:42.038
Doesn't matter now, does it?
It's too late.

13:42.691 --> 13:47.522
You know...
it doesn't have to be.

13:47.652 --> 13:52.832
You could buy me some time,
help save her <i>and</i>Laurent.

13:56.836 --> 13:58.750
Yeah. Right.

13:58.881 --> 14:00.709
[Chuckles softly]

14:02.711 --> 14:04.278
My wrist?

14:04.408 --> 14:05.540
Yeah.

14:08.282 --> 14:11.589
I'm gonna need your belt.

14:11.720 --> 14:13.722
Come on.

14:17.117 --> 14:19.859
Make it clean.
One cut.

14:23.645 --> 14:25.908
Yeah.
Come on.

14:26.039 --> 14:27.823
Right.

14:29.607 --> 14:31.261
You ready?

14:31.392 --> 14:33.307
Yeah.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

14:33.437 --> 14:35.918
Do something for me.

14:36.049 --> 14:38.225
You'll tell her
what I done for her.

14:40.096 --> 14:41.968
You got it.

14:42.098 --> 14:44.187
[Groans, cries]

14:48.017 --> 14:49.889
Let's go.
[Groans]

14:50.019 --> 14:51.107
[Blade scrapes]

14:51.238 --> 14:53.414
[Men shouting in distance]

14:53.544 --> 14:55.851
[Dramatic music plays]

15:00.987 --> 15:02.292
Aah!

15:02.423 --> 15:05.034
[Man grunts]

15:05.165 --> 15:07.776
[Shouts echoing in distance]

15:07.907 --> 15:15.479
♪♪

15:15.610 --> 15:17.960
[Men speaking French]

15:18.091 --> 15:25.315
♪♪

15:25.446 --> 15:28.144
[Indistinct shouting]

15:28.275 --> 15:33.280
♪♪

15:33.410 --> 15:36.109
[Vehicle passing]

15:36.239 --> 15:38.546
♪♪

15:38.676 --> 15:41.462
[Gurgling]

15:41.592 --> 15:47.294
♪♪

15:47.424 --> 15:53.300
♪♪

15:53.430 --> 15:56.433
Daryl!
Thank God.

15:56.564 --> 15:58.783
Have you seen Isabelle
and Laurent?

15:58.914 --> 15:59.784
No.

15:59.915 --> 16:01.264
Any idea
where they are?

16:01.395 --> 16:03.614
Cellblocks, I think.
I know how to get there.

16:03.745 --> 16:05.399
Can you get one of these cars
running?

16:05.529 --> 16:07.618
My uncle ran a garage.

16:07.749 --> 16:09.620
Great.
Hey, come here.

16:09.751 --> 16:13.755
♪♪

16:13.885 --> 16:15.322
Okay. Don't move.

16:15.452 --> 16:16.976
All right.

16:17.106 --> 16:18.020
[Metal clanks]

16:18.151 --> 16:23.765
♪♪

16:23.895 --> 16:25.854
[Indistinct conversations]

16:25.985 --> 16:31.294
♪♪

16:31.425 --> 16:36.604
♪♪

16:36.734 --> 16:38.954
Hey!

16:39.085 --> 16:40.869
Daryl.

16:41.870 --> 16:44.351
Get that pipe over there
and try to break the lock.

16:45.352 --> 16:47.963
[Walker hissing]

16:48.094 --> 16:49.965
Come on.
Isabelle!

16:50.096 --> 16:51.184
No.

16:51.314 --> 16:52.533
[Walker growling, snarling]

16:52.663 --> 16:56.232
♪♪

16:56.363 --> 16:58.582
[Grunts]

16:58.713 --> 17:00.802
[Walker snarling]

17:00.932 --> 17:02.325
[Screams]

17:02.456 --> 17:03.979
♪♪

17:04.110 --> 17:06.155
Hey! Hey!

17:06.286 --> 17:10.159
[Walkers growling]

17:11.943 --> 17:13.510
Take it. Take it.
You can save her.

17:13.641 --> 17:15.077
You can do this.
[Screams]

17:15.208 --> 17:16.296
You can save her.
You can do this.

17:16.426 --> 17:18.341
You can do it!
You can do this.

17:18.472 --> 17:20.213
You can do this.
Save her.

17:20.343 --> 17:21.953
Do it!
Save her!

17:22.084 --> 17:22.998
Save her!

17:23.129 --> 17:24.391
[Isabelle screams]

17:24.521 --> 17:26.306
Do it!

17:27.959 --> 17:30.397
Do it!

17:30.527 --> 17:32.312
[Walker growling]

17:32.442 --> 17:34.401
Laurent!

17:36.794 --> 17:38.057
God will forgive you.

17:38.187 --> 17:39.797
♪♪

17:39.928 --> 17:41.277
[Screams]

17:41.408 --> 17:43.062
Aah!

17:43.192 --> 17:45.238
[Blade slicing, body thuds]

17:45.368 --> 17:46.717
[Breathing heavily]

17:46.848 --> 17:48.719
[Blade clangs]

17:48.850 --> 17:51.244
[Down-tempo music plays]

17:51.374 --> 18:00.862
♪♪

18:04.039 --> 18:14.093
[Birds chirping]

18:18.923 --> 18:21.012
You know
where is the Nest?

18:21.143 --> 18:23.276
We know.

18:23.406 --> 18:25.278
Mm.

18:26.322 --> 18:27.236
Good luck.

18:27.367 --> 18:29.282
You too.
Thank you.

18:29.412 --> 18:31.719
[Down-tempo music plays]

18:31.849 --> 18:37.290
♪♪

18:37.420 --> 18:42.730
♪♪

18:42.860 --> 18:44.819
Fallou:
Ready.

18:44.949 --> 18:53.741
♪♪

18:53.871 --> 19:02.619
♪♪

19:02.750 --> 19:11.498
♪♪

19:11.628 --> 19:13.804
Isabelle:
Daryl.

19:13.935 --> 19:21.160
♪♪

19:21.290 --> 19:23.292
[Engine starts]

19:23.423 --> 19:30.604
♪♪

19:30.734 --> 19:38.002
♪♪

19:38.133 --> 19:42.181
Fallou ain't gonna let anything
happen to him.

19:44.705 --> 19:47.534
Have you ever been
in love?

19:50.798 --> 19:53.888
[Engine revs]

20:07.249 --> 20:11.732
It wasn't him anymore,
and he was never my father.

20:16.171 --> 20:19.479
Sometimes you have to do
horrible things,

20:19.609 --> 20:21.916
and no matter
how bad you feel,

20:22.046 --> 20:26.225
if there is no other choice,
God will forgive you.

20:27.487 --> 20:29.924
Like with my mother.

20:34.363 --> 20:37.148
[Engine sputtering]

20:37.279 --> 20:38.411
Oh, man.

20:38.541 --> 20:39.586
What is it?

20:39.716 --> 20:41.414
I don't know.

20:41.544 --> 20:43.764
[Engine sputtering]

20:47.942 --> 20:50.727
All right. I'm gonna have to
check this out.

21:01.738 --> 21:03.392
[Engine stops]

21:03.523 --> 21:05.960
[Metal scraping, clanking]

21:13.184 --> 21:17.101
My father tried to teach me
how to change a tire once.

21:17.232 --> 21:19.930
He gave up
after two hours.

21:20.061 --> 21:23.412
Mine used to have us
take apart engines.

21:23.543 --> 21:26.807
If we couldn't put them back
together, we got no dinner.

21:28.896 --> 21:30.158
That sounds hard.

21:30.289 --> 21:33.248
Yeah, it was --
when he was around.

21:33.379 --> 21:35.119
Which was hardly ever.

21:35.250 --> 21:37.426
He grew up
without a father.

21:37.557 --> 21:40.951
I guess history repeats itself
if you're not careful.

21:41.082 --> 21:43.171
You got that screwdriver?

21:46.348 --> 21:47.610
Ah.
Thank you.

21:47.741 --> 21:50.918
What do you mean,
history repeats itself?

21:51.048 --> 21:53.747
Mm.
My grandfather died here.

21:53.877 --> 21:55.270
In the war?

21:55.401 --> 21:57.403
Yeah.

21:57.533 --> 21:58.665
You never said.

21:58.795 --> 22:00.101
There's not much
to say.

22:00.231 --> 22:01.842
He enlisted,

22:01.972 --> 22:04.801
left his pregnant wife
back home -- my grandma --

22:04.932 --> 22:07.674
never came back.

22:07.804 --> 22:09.415
He gave his life
for France.

22:09.545 --> 22:13.027
Yeah, while his family
fell apart back home.

22:13.157 --> 22:14.420
Hardly seems worth it.

22:14.550 --> 22:16.900
Fighting for
what you believe?

22:17.031 --> 22:18.554
Wasn't much of a fight.

22:18.685 --> 22:21.514
[Exhales sharply]
He never made it off the beach.

22:22.602 --> 22:23.646
I'm sorry.

22:23.777 --> 22:25.039
Don't be.

22:29.260 --> 22:31.219
He's changed so much
since he met you.

22:31.350 --> 22:33.874
[Metal rattling, door closes]

22:34.831 --> 22:38.313
Mm.
Kids grow up.

22:39.096 --> 22:41.185
I didn't have much
to do with that.

22:41.316 --> 22:44.667
He's never had that kind
of influence in his life.

22:45.973 --> 22:48.541
I guess growing up with
no father was better than Quinn.

22:51.631 --> 22:53.894
Quinn thought about you
before he died.

22:54.024 --> 22:56.984
[Metal rattling]

22:57.114 --> 22:58.899
Did he ask you
to tell me that?

23:00.683 --> 23:03.382
Nah. I just thought
you should know.

23:07.081 --> 23:09.126
[Sniffs]

23:09.997 --> 23:11.781
You know, at first,
I was afraid of you.

23:11.912 --> 23:14.175
Why?
There's something in your eyes.

23:14.305 --> 23:17.744
I could tell you've been
through stuff.

23:17.874 --> 23:19.398
Your scars.

23:21.225 --> 23:23.010
I could tell
that you were dangerous.

23:23.140 --> 23:25.360
[Chuckles]

23:25.491 --> 23:27.449
That you could get us
where we needed to go.

23:27.580 --> 23:29.538
Well, I'm glad
I could help.

23:38.068 --> 23:40.593
[Exhales deeply,
grunts]

23:41.942 --> 23:43.857
There's something else
I have to confess.

23:43.987 --> 23:46.947
[Bolt clicking]

23:48.949 --> 23:50.298
I lied to you.

23:50.429 --> 23:52.126
Oh, yeah?
About what?

23:52.256 --> 23:54.041
[Grunts]

23:54.171 --> 23:56.783
About that picture
on the beach.

23:59.655 --> 24:02.571
I asked Laurent to draw that
once you got to the abbey.

24:03.703 --> 24:05.618
I thought it might convince you
to help us.

24:05.748 --> 24:07.794
[Chuckles softly]
Yeah.

24:08.621 --> 24:11.537
It was stupid.

24:11.667 --> 24:14.061
I don't know.
Was it?

24:14.191 --> 24:17.107
[Grunts]
I'm here now.

24:18.108 --> 24:21.372
It's not because
of your picture, either.

24:21.503 --> 24:24.506
Hey, can you hand me that --
that big wrench?

24:24.637 --> 24:27.074
[Metal scraping]

24:27.204 --> 24:29.293
Isabelle.

24:30.033 --> 24:31.818
Isabelle.

24:35.343 --> 24:36.997
[Sighs]

24:37.998 --> 24:38.955
Isabelle.

24:39.086 --> 24:40.740
Looking for this?

24:40.870 --> 24:43.177
[Grunts]

24:43.307 --> 24:44.831
[Dramatic music plays]

24:44.961 --> 24:47.311
♪♪

24:47.442 --> 24:48.356
[Wrench clatters]

24:48.487 --> 24:49.662
No, no, no.
Don't do this.

24:49.792 --> 24:50.880
Please.
I-I'll go with you.

24:51.011 --> 24:53.666
Sorry.
Madame said you all die today.

24:53.796 --> 24:55.189
The boy first.

24:55.319 --> 24:56.103
[Grunts]

24:56.233 --> 24:57.626
Laurent: Isabelle!

24:57.757 --> 24:59.672
Isabelle!

25:04.067 --> 25:05.460
♪♪

25:05.591 --> 25:08.028
Isabelle: <i>Il m'enverra</i>
<i>du ciel le salut...</i>

25:08.158 --> 25:10.030
No, no, no, no, no.

25:10.160 --> 25:13.424
I...I'm sorry.

25:13.555 --> 25:15.252
Don't do this.
Please. I'll go with you.

25:15.383 --> 25:16.602
Man:
<i>Dieu vous aime.</i>

25:16.732 --> 25:18.517
No, no, no, no.
[Breathing heavily]

25:18.647 --> 25:20.867
Sylvie:
[Speaking French]

25:22.869 --> 25:32.139
♪♪

25:32.269 --> 25:35.229
[Music builds, continues]

25:35.359 --> 25:38.798
♪♪

25:38.928 --> 25:40.408
No, no, no, no.

25:40.539 --> 25:42.584
[Music slows, continues]

25:42.715 --> 25:45.718
[Gasps,
breathing heavily]

25:45.848 --> 25:50.505
♪♪

25:50.636 --> 25:55.336
♪♪

25:55.466 --> 25:58.165
Not today, Dixon.

25:58.295 --> 25:59.253
Next time.

25:59.383 --> 26:08.088
♪♪

26:08.218 --> 26:16.313
♪♪

26:16.444 --> 26:18.402
Mont-Saint-Michel.

26:20.491 --> 26:21.928
The Nest?

26:23.712 --> 26:26.193
A day's walk north.

26:26.323 --> 26:28.804
Not even.

26:28.935 --> 26:30.545
[Down-tempo music plays]

26:30.676 --> 26:36.159
♪♪

26:36.290 --> 26:38.466
Burn the truck.

26:38.597 --> 26:40.599
Easy to track.

26:40.729 --> 26:44.907
[Music continues,
group singing in French]

26:45.038 --> 26:53.046
♪♪

