30:45.017 --> 30:47.846
Daryl:
Come on. All right. Guns up.

30:49.543 --> 30:51.719
Open.
[Guns cocking]

30:51.850 --> 30:53.025
Close.

30:54.853 --> 30:57.594
And fire.

30:57.725 --> 31:00.989
That's right.
Open. Close.

31:01.120 --> 31:02.817
Aim.
Stick it in your shoulder.

31:02.948 --> 31:05.820
[Children laughing]

31:05.951 --> 31:07.996
All right.
In your shoulder, like this.

31:08.127 --> 31:09.084
Open it.

31:09.215 --> 31:10.869
Issa!

31:17.136 --> 31:18.528
Guns up.

31:18.659 --> 31:20.748
Open.
[Guns cocking]

31:22.141 --> 31:24.143
Close.

31:24.273 --> 31:25.361
Fire.

31:26.885 --> 31:28.582
[Down-tempo music plays]

31:28.712 --> 31:30.236
Guns up.

31:31.411 --> 31:33.108
Open.
[Guns cocking]

31:33.239 --> 31:35.937
Shut it.
Raise them up.

31:36.068 --> 31:37.156
Fire.

31:37.286 --> 31:39.636
[Music continues,
group vocalizing]

31:39.767 --> 31:42.074
[Birds squawking]

31:43.249 --> 31:45.991
Losang:
What makes us human?

31:46.121 --> 31:48.863
Laurent: Aristotle said humans
have the ability to reason.

31:48.994 --> 31:51.605
That's right.
Rationality.

31:51.735 --> 31:54.173
Yeah. It's so good.
Wow.

31:54.303 --> 31:55.435
<i>Santé.</i>

31:55.565 --> 31:58.829
♪♪

31:58.960 --> 32:00.657
<i>Santé.</i>

32:00.788 --> 32:02.877
<i>Santé.</i> <i>Santé. </i><i>Santé. </i><i>Santé.</i>

32:03.008 --> 32:11.930
♪♪

32:12.060 --> 32:15.803
[Laurent laughing,
Daryl speaking indistinctly]

32:15.934 --> 32:25.508
♪♪

32:25.639 --> 32:27.467
[Laughs]

32:27.597 --> 32:29.512
♪♪

32:29.643 --> 32:31.993
There.
Not even close.

32:32.124 --> 32:35.127
Losang: We are led to believe in
the belief of a supreme being,

32:35.257 --> 32:40.306
but God does not exist
unless we believe in God.

32:40.436 --> 32:41.742
Okay.

32:41.872 --> 32:43.831
But God is not a deceiver,

32:43.962 --> 32:49.271
and we are beings capable of
individual thought and reason.

32:49.402 --> 32:57.497
♪♪

32:57.627 --> 33:05.809
♪♪

33:05.940 --> 33:14.079
♪♪

33:14.209 --> 33:17.604
I'm sorry.
I, uh, didn't mean to interrupt.

33:17.734 --> 33:18.692
Wait.

33:20.563 --> 33:22.043
Can you help me?

33:22.174 --> 33:24.524
I can't reach my back.

33:26.743 --> 33:29.181
Sure.

33:36.492 --> 33:38.494
[Water splashing]

33:44.065 --> 33:45.458
[Chair sliding]

33:45.588 --> 33:47.851
[Clears throat]

33:50.419 --> 33:51.377
Oof.

33:51.507 --> 33:53.466
Is it that bad?

33:53.596 --> 33:57.165
It's a pretty impressive
battle wound for a nun.

33:58.862 --> 34:01.822
I think you said
"killer nun."

34:01.952 --> 34:03.302
Killer nun.

34:03.432 --> 34:05.565
[Water splashing]

34:07.480 --> 34:10.222
Do you like it here?

34:10.352 --> 34:12.920
It's not
what I expected.

34:13.790 --> 34:16.141
What did you expect?

34:16.271 --> 34:19.144
Bunch of Amish people
running around.

34:19.274 --> 34:22.451
Straw hats,
people churning butter, bonnets.

34:22.582 --> 34:25.889
[Exhales deeply]
It hurts to laugh.

34:26.020 --> 34:28.066
[Water splashing]

34:29.850 --> 34:31.417
I like it here.

34:34.028 --> 34:35.551
Yeah.

34:35.682 --> 34:37.423
Kind of grows on you.

34:40.121 --> 34:42.428
Feels like home.

34:46.780 --> 34:48.260
Losang:
Now, I was skeptical

34:48.390 --> 34:51.176
when Pere Jean first sent word
of the boy,

34:51.306 --> 34:53.961
but I decided to do the
pilgrim's camino to Santiago,

34:54.092 --> 34:57.269
so I stopped at the Abbaye
de Bernadette to meet him,

34:57.399 --> 34:58.922
and I knew.

35:00.315 --> 35:01.708
Yeah.
He's a good kid.

35:01.838 --> 35:03.536
Who looks up to you.

35:03.666 --> 35:05.320
And he's here
because of you.

35:05.451 --> 35:07.017
Well, Isabelle, really.

35:07.148 --> 35:09.411
Well, we're grateful
to you both,

35:09.542 --> 35:12.284
and...I'm sorry
to see you go.

35:14.416 --> 35:17.027
You kept your word.
We've kept ours.

35:17.158 --> 35:19.421
Found a vessel
to help get you home.

35:19.552 --> 35:22.511
Fishermen from Dover.
Safe passage to England.

35:22.642 --> 35:26.124
They know of boats that can
get you as far as Newfoundland.

35:26.254 --> 35:28.474
You'll have to manage
from there.

35:28.604 --> 35:30.476
When does it leave?

35:30.606 --> 35:32.478
It'll be there
in two days.

35:32.608 --> 35:34.523
You'll have to walk
to the north coast.

35:34.654 --> 35:37.961
Uh, so...set out at dawn.

35:38.092 --> 35:40.225
[Down-tempo music plays]

35:40.355 --> 35:43.053
Unless you've changed
your mind.

35:43.184 --> 35:45.186
Well, I-I got family
waiting for me back home.

35:45.317 --> 35:46.753
Well,
you've got people here

35:46.883 --> 35:48.668
who'll hope you stay.

35:48.798 --> 35:51.758
♪♪

35:51.888 --> 35:53.499
It's not so easy.

35:53.629 --> 35:57.546
♪♪

35:57.677 --> 36:00.288
Who knows what tomorrow
will bring?

36:00.419 --> 36:06.599
And an ocean away,
the world being what it is.

36:06.729 --> 36:11.517
But we need you --
here, now.

36:11.647 --> 36:13.867
♪♪

36:13.997 --> 36:17.523
Pouvoir --
It isn't my fight.

36:17.653 --> 36:20.569
♪♪

36:20.700 --> 36:24.704
Maybe the fight's
not the reason you're torn.

36:24.834 --> 36:28.925
Sometimes, when a person
leaves home,

36:29.056 --> 36:31.537
he comes to find
he belongs someplace else.

36:31.667 --> 36:36.063
♪♪

37:50.093 --> 37:58.624
<i>No, Madame.</i>

37:58.754 --> 38:02.149
[Down-tempo music plays]

38:06.632 --> 38:14.901
♪♪

